<p><strong>Bug C</strong> — The program crashes because Pygame is given a position with a decimal point.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">ship_x = ship_x + velocity_x
pygame.draw.rect(screen, CYAN, (ship_x - 20, ship_y, 40, 50))
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> velocity is a decimal; screen positions must be whole numbers.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
